transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I have a question, I just got a prescription received and I ordered the new pill, the AGV.

Speaker 2: Pill.

Speaker 1: When I got it last time it said AGV on the bottle, this time it didn't say it, is it—

Speaker 2: The same prescription?

Speaker 1: Let me double check, I'm trying to pull your information up with the phone number that—

Speaker 2: I have, 908-358-7498?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, on the actual pill, what's on the back of the pill, I can tell you what you received—

Speaker 1: Actually.

Speaker 2: It's got a couple of letters on the back of it, you know, on the back of the pill itself?

Speaker 1: Yes, the back of the pill itself.

Speaker 2: I have to get the bottle, hang on.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: The last time it said it on the prescription thing, it said AGV, the next time it says—

Speaker 1: Demerit.

Speaker 2: Did you order online or did you actually call in?

Speaker 1: I ordered online and the online had it in there.

Speaker 2: Yes, to get the AGV you have to be on some type of prescription plan and I'm looking—

Speaker 1: At the counter, you're not on any type of prescription plan with this, but I can go—

Speaker 2: Ahead and take care of that for you.

Speaker 1: I'll go ahead and get that replaced for you with the correct AGV, but to get the AGV—

Speaker 2: Because it's such a popular pill, you have to have some type of prescription.

Speaker 1: It doesn't have to be every month, but you can set up to like even twice a year, like—

Speaker 2: Once every six months, but in order to get the AGV, since it is such a popular pill that—

Speaker 1: Everybody wants, we do require our regular customers to have some type of plan to get—

Speaker 2: That particular pill, so otherwise you would just get the generic pill, but I'm going to—

Speaker 1: Take care of you this time, but if I do that, it's okay if I put you out for like every—

Speaker 2: Five or six months and you can always call.

Speaker 1: Do twice a year.

Speaker 2: Yeah, there is writing on this pill.

Speaker 1: Yeah, but it's not the number that you're looking for.

Speaker 2: I can tell you right now, I'm looking at your account.

Speaker 1: I'm looking at the account now, you got the generic Viagra, you didn't get the AGV.

Speaker 2: Okay, I want the AGV.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm going to send that out to you for no charge and I'll push it out for every six—

Speaker 2: Months going forward, all right?

Speaker 1: All right, sounds good.

Speaker 2: The AGV is going to have numbers on the back, not the letters.

Speaker 1: Yeah, this has, let me see what it has.

Speaker 2: You already know what it is, right?

Speaker 1: I already know what it is.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm looking at what you got.

Speaker 1: So my prescription said AGV on it.

Speaker 2: When I renewed it, it said the AGV pill.

Speaker 1: I'm telling you right now, if you don't have an automatic type of subscription on file—

Speaker 2: You're not going to get the AGV.

Speaker 1: You're not going to get it, okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, exactly.

Speaker 1: That's the whole point of that, all right?

Speaker 2: All right, so you could replace this and put me on it every six months.

Speaker 1: Exactly.

Speaker 2: That's what I'm going to do for you.

Speaker 1: So you should get the AGV within the next seven to ten days and then you're going to—

Speaker 2: Be every six months.

Speaker 1: But we're very flexible with that.

Speaker 2: Otherwise, if six months come too soon, just call us and say push me back a few more months.

Speaker 1: I'm not ready.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: And if you want to order before then, don't go online.

Speaker 2: Call us like you're doing now and then therefore you get the AGV going forward, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, sounds good.

Speaker 2: Yep, thank you.

Speaker 1: Not a problem.

Speaker 2: Take care.

Speaker 1: You too.
